text:
First of all, Oh Tain Tee is not the name of this coffeeshop. It’s name is actually Coffee Sense (咖啡鄉）initial post got it wrong.

Strange that such a small little ulu coffeeshop in AMK can gather so many reviews.

Non the less, I feel that this place is a hidden Jem. With good variety of food, clean and cooling natural wind even though it’s sunny right now.

The stalls mainly are: Indian food, porridge, carrot cake, roasted, fish soup, fish ball noodle, mix veg rice, seafood zhi char, claypot delights and western food. Not bad.
Quite surprising low rated kpt.. Tried the zha cai fan, fish soup, western food and claypot rice all taste very decent.. Drinks stall sell dessert too..

I like fish soup in coffee shop.the fish is fresh, a lot of vegetables and tomato.The soup is tasty. Nice.There is a grilled store that sells Western food , a noodle, a woonton Mee store and a zi Cha store that fry vegetables or pork or fish items upon ordering. Moderate crowd on days, more crowded during weekends.

Available here steak with Restaurant taste but hawker price, if you are hot pot fried rice fan you can have it here also with an average taste, seafood also available such as chilli crab/black pepper crab/steam fish for dinner. As for breakfast you can have fried hokkian mie, minched pork noodle and simple porridge. A must try drink is lemon tea here. Simple coffee shop
The Claypot rice and Bak Kut Teh is good. I have visited a few times with my colleagues.
